Johannesburg - Comedian Ndumiso Lindi is gearing up for his latest show, which is inspired by the death of his father who died a year ago. Lindi enjoyed great success with his recent shows, which include Diluted People, and Colour Mine, aired on Comedy Central. His upcoming one-man show, titled Boys Don't Cry in July, is inspired by the passing of his late father Isaiah Lungile Lindi, who died in July last year. The show will celebrates his fatherâ€™s life by Lindi using comedy as a tool that will help him come to terms with the loss. His dad was 76 at his time of death. 